
 \Slocate\S: Find UNIX System Commands with Keywords

     Give \Slocate\S one or more keywords related  to  the  work
     you  want  to  do.  It  will print a list of UNIX system commands
     whose actions are related  to  the  keywords.  

     For example, you enter the keywords \Sprint file\S 

    \Slocate\S could produce the list:   The cat (concatenate) command
                                         The ls (list) command
                                         The pr (print) command

     Enter a \Sk\S to use \Slocate\S. 

              choices            description

                \S k \S              Enter a list of keywords

                \S r \S              Redirect to a file or a command
                \S q \S              Quit
